<title>UK: Eversholt directors profiteering - UK's Blair.</title>
<headline>Eversholt directors profiteering - UK's Blair.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-02-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>Labour leader Tony Blair on Tuesday accused directors of train-leasing company Eversholt Leasing of profiteering by selling the company some 14 months after it was privatised.</p>
<p>Blair told parliament Eversholt would be sold shortly for 900 million stg, compared with the privatisation price at the end of 1995 of 580 million. &quot;Such profits are entirely unjustified,&quot; he said at Prime Minister's question time.</p>
<p>Press reports have suggested Forward Trust, a subsidiary of HSBC Holdings, will buy Eversholt. Labour Party sources said they expected an announcement on Wednesday.</p>
